# Typography file workflow

Composite typography is defined once in JSON and emitted to CSS/TS. Do not maintain parallel copies in component modules.

## Source of truth

| File | Role |
|------|------|
| `packages/ui/src/tokens/armada-tokens.json` | **Edit here** — `semantic.typography.*` composites |
| `packages/ui/src/styles/tokens.css` | Hand-maintained colors/spacing; **imports** generated typography |

## Generated (do not hand-edit)

| File | Produced by |
|------|-------------|
| `packages/ui/src/styles/typography.css` | `npm run tokens:typography --workspace=@armada/ui` |
| `packages/ui/src/typography/variants.ts` | same command |

Generated output includes `--semantic-typography-*` CSS variables and `.armada-text-*` utility classes.

## Workflow

1. Change composites only in `armada-tokens.json`.
2. From repo root: `npm run tokens:typography --workspace=@armada/ui`
3. Commit JSON **and** both generated files together.
4. **Never** hand-edit `typography.css` or `variants.ts`.

Apps import composites via `@armada/ui/styles/tokens.css` (which pulls in `typography.css`).

